## Context
scripts/analyze_multilingual.py computes isolation scores, quadrant classification
(English/non-English x Global North/South per OECD DAC), citation directionality,
and language x cluster contingency. It reads refined_works.csv, embeddings.npz,
and citations.csv — all existing Phase 1 outputs. No GPU needed.

Makefile rule: `make content/tables/multilingual_report.json`

## Actions
1. SSH to padme, run the Makefile target
2. Sync report back to doudou via `make corpus-sync`
3. Inspect output: quadrant counts, unclassified fraction, isolation means

## Test
multilingual_report.json exists and contains keys: language_stats, quadrant_stats,
isolation_k10, citation_flows, contingency, core_composition.

## Exit criteria
Report generated on padme and pulled to doudou.
